{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17519157","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17519157"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T14:09:35+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T14:09:35+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12984"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"12984","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/12984"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.61,0.22,0.04,0.01,0.13]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5422"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"39159"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"5422","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/5422"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12984"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"23482"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"1044"},{"type":"tags","id":"4578"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"9168"},{"type":"contributions","id":"9934"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35377"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"39159","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/39159"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 50-year-old woman presents with diarrhea, abdominal cramps, and fatigue for the last 4 months. She has had 6kg of weight loss in the last 6 months. She reports no fever, chills, or rectal bleeding. Her past medical history includes Hashimoto\u0027s thyroiditis, cholelithiasis, and hypertension. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, her blood pressure is 115/75 mmHg, pulse 67/min, respiratory rate 13/min, and temperature 37 C. She has mild conjunctival pallor. Her abdominal examination is unremarkable.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEndoscopy with small bowel biopsy shows villous atrophy with crypt hyperplasia and intraepithelial lymphocytes. Tissue transglutaminase IgA is positive.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Given the most likely diagnosis, which human leukocyte antigen (HLA) haplotype is most strongly associated with this patient\u0027s condition?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["HLA-DQ2","HLA-B27","HLA-DRB1","HLA-DPB1","HLA-DR3"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ECoeliac disease is a chronic immune-mediated enteropathy triggered by exposure to dietary gluten in genetically predisposed individuals. Many genes involved in the pathogenesis have been identified, and the Human Leukocyte Antigen (HLA) system is known to play a crucial role. Approximately, 85% of coeliac patients possess at least one copy of \u003Cstrong\u003EHLA-DQ2,\u003C/strong\u003E 5\u201310% one copy of HLA-DQ8, and less than 5% just a half of the heterodimer DQ2, more often DQB1*02. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHLA-B27\u003C/strong\u003E is associated with ankylosing spondylitis, reactive arthritis, Behcet disease, inflammatory bowel disease, and psoriatic arthritis. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHLA-DRB1 and DPB1\u003C/strong\u003E are associated with rheumatoid arthritis. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe class II gene products,\u003Cstrong\u003E HLA-DR3\u003C/strong\u003E and DR4, may be the primary susceptibility genes for type 1 diabetes mellitus.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Celiac disease development is strongly linked to the presence of HLA-DQ2 and/or DQ8, which present the immunogenic gluten peptides and trigger the immune response leading to pathogenesis."],"references":["Sciurti M, Fornaroli F, Gaiani F, Bonaguri C, Leandro G, Di Mario F, De\u0027 Angelis GL. Genetic susceptibility and celiac disease: what role do HLA haplotypes play? Acta Biomed. 2018 Dec 17;89(9-S):17-21.","Tolone, C., Piccirillo, M., Dolce, P. et al. Celiac disease in pediatric patients according to HLA genetic risk classes: a retrospective observational study. Ital J Pediatr 47, 107 (2021)."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"23482"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12984"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"23482","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/23482"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2023-08-30T12:43:09+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-04T20:20:49+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5422"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"39159"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"65","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/65"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Investigations","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonyms":null,"description":"Only suitable for a graduating medical student at the end of their degree","position":1,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"1044","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1044"},"attributes